:: Reduce demand by making local public transportation free [correct-answer] {"position":"500,1900","size":"100,100"}
This is a fantastic policy - it will put more money back into people's pockets, and will help better connect rural communities and cities outside of London alike. The UK public transport network has been extensively privatised and is run in the interests of profit, not service. So rather than giving subsidies to private companies, the government can re-nationalise these services, improving wages and increasing the desirability of these jobs in the local communities.

We'd quickly overwhelm the Earth's resources if we tried to replace every petrol car out there with an electric equivalent. But if we make public transportation a true alternative to owning a car, we can persuade people to ditch their private vehicles and greatly reduce the total amount of resources that we need to give everyone a good life.

