:: Set up Citizen‚Äôs Assembly networks [correct-answer] {"position":"450,475","size":"100,100"}
You have the right instincts - our current system of representative politics doesn't result in popular policies (such as the re-nationalisation of our public services) becoming reality. By making our democracy more participatory, we‚Äôll make sure that these important policies are prioritised by government, while ensuring people feel more connected to their communities and more in control of their lives.

We could set these up via sortition (so any adult in the country could be selected to be part of the assembly), setting terms for a period of several years. It would also be important to train and pay people to participate, so any inequalities up until now are not exacerbated in this process, as well as minimising financial hardship from not working.

From here on in, let‚Äôs assume that the choices you‚Äôre making are on policy areas that the public are raising as those that need to be addressed, and that they‚Äôve had a chance to input their thoughts into what the solutions should be ‚ú® let‚Äôs keep going!

